main event: On 13 March-April 1964, witnesses reported observing an unidentified object with blinking lights moving at high speeds.
interesting points: The object had a pulsating, blinking white light and was estimated to be about the size of a car., The sighting occurred at night, limiting visibility and details., Witnesses described a humming sound associated with the object., The object was visible for approximately 10 to 15 seconds before disappearing., No conclusive determinations about the object's nature or origin could be made.
sighted object: a lighted object with blinking lights
witness description: The witness described the object as moving rapidly and hovering without leaving any visible trail.
